At 01:57 PM 5/7/2002, Billy wrote:

>There's still a cam follower, but it's different (why?)

It's made up of several parts and holds oil.  Its length adjusts 
automatically to remove valve lash.

>Is there no pushrod in there, just oil pushing the valves open?

No, there is still a pushrod.  It's a thinner, steel pushrod (solid lifer 
rods are aluminum).

